subSubSection.paragraph:
Female
. Head (
Fig. 22B
) smaller than male; clypeus not beyond anterior margin of supra-antennal ridges; temples extremely obsolete. Mandible (
Fig. 22D
) slenderer and with apex pointed.

Abdominal sternite VII not protruding on posterior margin. Sternite VIII (
Fig. 22G
) with posterior margin weakly bi-emarginate near middle. Tergite X (
Fig. 22I
) with posterior margin truncate but not so narrow as male.

Spermatheca (
Fig. 22J
) C-shaped, right-angled at near middle, basal portion slightly inflated, gradually narrowed apically, and apical portion curved, with apex rounded.

Distribution. China ( Beijing , Fujian , Guizhou , Hong Kong , Jiangxi, Liaoning, Shanghai, Sichuan, Taiwan , Zhejiang); South Korea ; Japan ; Myanmar ; Indonesia ; Pakistan ; India ; Sri Lanka ; Nepal ; Bangladesh ; Egypt (for
O. varipennis ssp. pharaonum
).
